OL,6, Today's continuity announcers are      
OL,7, following in the footsteps of their    
OL,8, predecessors - though they don't have  
OL,9, the same work from years ago as now    
OL,10, it's mainly computerised, whereas the  
OL,11, old announcers did a lot of the work   
OL,12, themselves live. So let's embrace the  
OL,13, era of announcers from years gone by.  
OL,14, Sadly quite a lot are now gone but we  
OL,15, can cherish the memories of their witty
OL,16, and wonderful announcements and their  
OL,17, bloopers and suchlike.                 
OL,19, As an announcer would sign off... This 
OL,20, is Amy Lou McCloughan wishing you all a
OL,21, safe and peaceful day for tomorrow.    
OL,22, Goodnight and sleep well.              
